
'''= sum of digital network access capacity per square kilometer'''


=Policy recommendations=

Jaap van Till [http://www.han.nl/lectoraat/telecom]:

"What to do - Set a target for the improvement of Teledensity ( sum of digital network access capacity / square
kilometer) in the USA and elsewhere.

How- If a chart is made in rank order of teledensity versus area's it can be seen that the variation is immense
between the city center of New York and up in the mountains and in the jungle of Sumatra.
       
There is no way this ranking can be flattened, since the dynamic character of this rankdistribution an attempt to
do so will simply change the places of the players and will result in a graph with a similar skewed shape.
       
I recommend to make such chart for the USA and then set a target to LIFT the whole graph in a significant
percentage in a certain timeframe. Say 50% in 4 years.


Why- The positive effects on the creation of wealth and social fabric of broadband connections between companies
and civilians is well known and is a sound investment for the common good.
       
A effort should be made to lift the graph by a similar percentage outside the USA in a joint effort with other
states also, since connectvity over there is beneficial for all, also over here."
(http://cookreport.com/mailman/private/arch-econ_cookreport.com/)


